    <br>
    <br>
    a. Can you <b><u>bury</u></b> the box in the back garden? <i>(bury/berry)</i>
    <br>
    <br>
    b. Alex could not <b><u>break</u></b> the branch off the tree. <i>(break/brake)</i>
    <br>
    <br>
    c. <b><u>Whose</u></b> pencil is on the floor? <i>(Who's/Whose)</i>
    <br>
    <br>
    d. We have got very <b><u>few</u></b> <i>(phew/few)</i> tasks left.
    <br>
    <br>
    e. Some tribes worship their gods before they <b><u>prey</u></b>. <i>(prey/pray)</i>
    <br>
    <br>
    f. <b><u>Damn</u></b> it. Everything is messed up. <i>(Dam /Damn)</i>
    <br>
    <br>
    g. What a wonderful <b><u>lesson</u></b> the professor presented. <i>(lesson/lessen)</i>
